<h1>Tokens</h1>
<p>Design tokens are the visual design atoms of the design system â€” specifically, they are named entities that store visual design attributes. We use them in place of hard-coded values (such as hex values for color or pixel values for spacing) in order to maintain a scalable and consistent visual system for UI development.</p>
<hr>
<% sage_tokens.each do |token| %>
  <h3><%= token[:category] %></h3>
  <h6>Default</h6>
  <div class="tokens">
     <div class="token token-<%= token[:category] %>"><strong>sage-<%= token[:category] %>( )</strong></div>
  </div>
  <h6>Options</h6>
  <div class="tokens">
    <% token[:tokens] .each do |test| %>
      <div class="token token-<%= token[:category] %>-<%= test[:name] %>"><strong>sage-<%= token[:category] %>(<%= test[:name] %>)</strong></div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
<% end %>